[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring JSON field order**\n\nI’m thinking about how Json literals maintain object field insertion order through JsonObject, and arrays preserve their order too. I wonder if this feature has been directly tested. Some tests focus on array order, not object orders, and there could be potential bugs if fields are reversed. It seems like the behavior with Circe’s JsonObject may not have comprehensive tests that cover this aspect. Perhaps I should think about writing a test to specifically check for the source order of literal and interpolated object fields.\n\n**Considering test focus**\n\nI’m thinking that to avoid duplicating re-test classes, I should focus on the order rather than the key/value encoding. I wonder if I can make assertions on the order of keys and arrays, since the array order is already covered by `downN`, but object order isn’t. I need to check whether Circe guarantees the order of keys in `JsonObject`. It seems relevant, especially if the documentation states that insertion order is preserved. I hope that’s ok!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cf9dfbf15a03703016a2a3a4d231481959912621fbfb84e37\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKjpd6YCH-d-8tfWJZALnFiJtUXT5w0wGeLdZCgMW2lBYxSqXJKoJLr6WVtXA8uDbsiCop5c9Cxh5tuSDBEDB-AO9yurNz-Xl5oQpDL_hOiX1iz6Rx2VkRNJsa9z9tY6oiX5ZbWbdoZzY8bIpVqXMr--aVSWrEIaBwCGvLpAhJzVtlp0-Yg-WXwCBZy_VX3F14RNAZ7-Zpf4GzZ6WbdIDMi-cUYjuQJAY24Az_Re53fHhfTVdVOwjL5Q7KOr8vP90uBZt9tSup0LdRA8FdWY6JoR8OdbF0g0YsUZZFu8MyindkIHnHh9brGR41eNiLd0bLx56c4jJE7QBLTbnumHBo_zP01WV3teGO65xhiqRtJTuZ8gd5U_k91SVkMjwCt2BUkl1pkyS14Gf49uRaheBCgbTwGOXv6ohymLkohzn0FpZBFHNNcRkFrKzBS3o8_WxfqDTnru0eGMHdcNnKaRC2-CZWrPB8Av9Sje-vWLZAzABfc8XTt0R636qE0Y5dBGgEqFiZiuQUPMh-hllfLTLHxESouWVKCqUVRDhkMvPgP9Qjn6KwhWA850F0e1h-DzgklkApC8zX-yTQ2riVBgY6Q9Uu0CnluBHn0zQ3V05o88yssaO9pldvUYV6kWQNsv6R2vmsfe9Zw-eglQ3aS9T4zU_KdWlgcxLMIgqxi6aF63c